  "prompt": "What's Home Depot's return/exchange policy?",
  "response": "As of my last update in October 2023, Home Depot's return and exchange policy generally includes the following:\n\n1. **Standard Returns**: \n   - Home Depot typically accepts returns within 90 days of purchase.\n   - Items must be returned in their original condition and packaging.\n   - Proof of purchase is usually required, such as a receipt.\n\n2. **Exceptions**:\n   - Certain items may have shorter return windows or different requirements, such as electronics, major appliances, and furniture.\n   - Custom-made or special order items might not be returnable.\n   \n3. **Online Purchases**:\n   - Items bought online can often be returned through the mail or at any Home Depot store.\n   - Return shipping might be free for some products under certain conditions.\n\n4. **Defective or Damaged Items**:\n   - If an item is defective or damaged, Home Depot generally offers a replacement, repair, or refund.\n   \n5. **Credit**:\n   - Refunds are typically issued in the original form of payment.\n   - If you used a Home Depot store credit, your refund might be issued as store credit.\n\n6. **Store Credit**:\n   - In some cases, returns without a receipt may be eligible for store credit at the lowest selling price within the last 90 days.\n\nFor the most accurate and up-to-date information, including specific conditions and exceptions, you should check Home Depot's official website or contact their customer service directly.",
